<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1585,2012]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1745,1771]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Laterally compressed lamellar form, resembling an axe, with marginal oscula. Specimens stay lighter-coloured (beige) in ethanol.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1585,2012]" box="[198,343,1825,1851]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,1825,1851]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1585,2012]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Laterally compressed lamellar form, resembling an axe with maximum dimensions of 
<quantity box="[1215,1273,1866,1892]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="cm" value="7.0">7 cm</quantity>
in length, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="cm" value="5.8">5.8 cm</quantity>
in width and 
<quantity box="[347,426,1906,1932]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="cm" value="0.8">0.8 cm</quantity>
in thickness, with a very narrow base (
<figureCitation box="[882,991,1906,1932]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,255,1314,1338]" captionTargetBox="[268,1314,325,1264]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[264,1323,317,1288]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13: A – D. Aplysina pergamentacea Hechtel, 1983 — Holotype (YPM 9004). A – B. habit after preservation. C. Skeletal architecture. D. Spongin fibres. Scale bars = A. 2 cm, B. 0.5 cm, C. 500 µm, D. 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178890/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[936,966,1906,1932]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="13.0">13</number>
A
</figureCitation>
). The oscula are located marginally in the sponge (
<figureCitation box="[295,395,1946,1972]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,255,1314,1338]" captionTargetBox="[268,1314,325,1264]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[264,1323,317,1288]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13: A – D. Aplysina pergamentacea Hechtel, 1983 — Holotype (YPM 9004). A – B. habit after preservation. C. Skeletal architecture. D. Spongin fibres. Scale bars = A. 2 cm, B. 0.5 cm, C. 500 µm, D. 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178890/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[345,374,1946,1972]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="13.0">13</number>
B
</figureCitation>
). The surface is slightly/finely conulose. Colour after preservation in alcohol is reddishbrown. Consistency is compressible and elastic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,151,261]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,305,151,177]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Skeleton</emphasis>
: Choanosome formed by an irregular polygonal reticulation of spongin fibers (
<figureCitation box="[1252,1361,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,255,1314,1338]" captionTargetBox="[268,1314,325,1264]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[264,1323,317,1288]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13: A – D. Aplysina pergamentacea Hechtel, 1983 — Holotype (YPM 9004). A – B. habit after preservation. C. Skeletal architecture. D. Spongin fibres. Scale bars = A. 2 cm, B. 0.5 cm, C. 500 µm, D. 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178890/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number box="[1309,1339,152,178]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="13.0">13</number>
C
</figureCitation>
), with amber coloured bark and thickness of 
<number box="[599,672,192,218]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="68.5" valueMax="95.0" valueMin="42.0">42–95</number>
Μm (average 
<number box="[835,864,192,218]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="69.0">69</number>
Μm). The pith can be black or amber, 
<number box="[1315,1389,192,218]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="21.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="12.0">12–30</number>
Μm (average 
<number box="[259,288,232,258]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="19.0">19</number>
Μm, 
<figureCitation box="[350,457,232,258]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,255,1314,1338]" captionTargetBox="[268,1314,325,1264]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[264,1323,317,1288]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13: A – D. Aplysina pergamentacea Hechtel, 1983 — Holotype (YPM 9004). A – B. habit after preservation. C. Skeletal architecture. D. Spongin fibres. Scale bars = A. 2 cm, B. 0.5 cm, C. 500 µm, D. 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178890/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number box="[403,433,232,258]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="13.0">13</number>
D
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
